body_html: @martinwicke I think pre-TensorFlow 1.8, these XLA headers were not referenced by code outside of XLA, but now they are (even when not compiling with XLA). I think I saw some comments in the headers speaking about including the header to reduce code duplication. That must have introduced this bug.

body: @martinwicke I think pre-TensorFlow 1.8, these XLA headers were not referenced by code outside of XLA, but now they are (even when not compiling with XLA).
